<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <CalDefFileVersion>7</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>10/30/2015</Date>
    <Description>Added the following new CALs that have been confirmed to be needed to this CalDef file: 1.) Genre_Artist_Playlist_Slot_T1Threshold, 2.) Album_Slot_T2_Threshold, 3.) Album_Slot_T1_Threshold, 4.) SongType_Slot_T2_Threshold, and 5.) SongType_Slot_T1_Threshold; added SR_ENABLE_RDSSTATION for ASR control of FM station names </Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>3/3/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file for MY18 and beyond, added five new calibrations ( 1.) SR_ENABLE_RDSSTATION, 2.) Maximum_Size_Contact_Downloading, and 3.) Maximum_Size_Contact_User_Adding, 4.) PLEASE_WAIT_ACTIVE_TIMER, and 5.) SR_Min_Inter_Prompt_Time ) for SSE tuning thresholds.  </Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>7/1/2016</Date>
    <Description>Deleted previous SR_ENABLE_STATIC_TEXT_DISPLAY calibration (CalID:_NBSgMLhXEeSVLJ5Lfed1uw) since this EnumInger map calibration was tied to an enumberation in the LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.enumdef that is no longer being used. Created a new SR_ENABLE_STATIC_TEXT_DISPLAY calibration (CalID:_HwHJID-1EealxNeJxc3hmA) to a new enumeration in the GIS582_Speech_Recognition_Screen_Flows.enumdef file for use with this calibration. </Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>1/3/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#: 1652991, updated the SR_ENABLE_STATIC_TEXT_DISPLAY enumeration calibration within the GIS582_Speech_Recognition_Screen_Flows.caldef and GIS582_Speech_Recognition_Screen_Flows.enumdef to add an enumeration (PORTUGUESE_BRAZILIAN) for the Brazilian Portuguese language, since Brazilian Portugese is a required Speech Rec. language for MY19 and beyond.</Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="Is the system to display Speech Recognition screen 'Static' text on the CSM and/or Cluster displays, or just images and dynamic text? If Static text is NOT allowed (for a language) on the display, then the static screen text does not need to be localized for the language. If static text is disabled for a language, then only dynamic text from list screens (like NBEst lists and Disambiguation lists) will be displayed. Other screens will only show icons indicating the SR session state for listening window. Static text allowed on neither display = 0, Static text allowed on CSM = 1, Static text allowed on Cluster = 2, Static text allowed on Both = 3. " Name="SR_ENABLE_STATIC_TEXT_DISPLAY" References="GIS 582" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_HwHJID-1EealxNeJxc3hmA</CalID>
    <Type>EnumIntegerMap</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>1/3/2018</Date>
      <Description>Added an enumeration (PORTUGUESE_BRAZILIAN) for the Brazilian Portuguese language, since Brazilian Portugese is a required Speech Rec. language for MY19 and beyond.</Description>
      <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <EnumIntegerMap>
      <EnumID>_Abrg8D-vEeaIX5pSk5aPDw</EnumID>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>3</MaxValue>
      <Units>none</Units>
